{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01CAnTaKVSNMMnRqjcoptmJW","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The issue is clear. There are two problems with the ConfigMap:\n\n1. **Wrong seed hosts**: Using `default.svc.cluster.local` instead of `elasticsearch.svc.cluster.local`\n2. **Empty `node.name`**: The `node.name: ` is empty/blank, which is why es-cluster-2 fails with `null-valued setting found for key [node.name]`\n\nThe running nodes (es-cluster-0 and es-cluster-1) must have gotten the correct `node.name` from somewhere else - likely from the `POD_NAME` environment variable being substituted, but now the ConfigMap has an empty `node.name` value.\nThe `${POD_NAME}` variable substitution in the ConfigMap appears to have failed, leaving `node.name` empty when es-cluster-2 tried to start. The earlier pods might have been running with a previous configuration or obtained their node names through a different mechanism. I need to check how the StatefulSet injects environment variables into the pods to understand where the node name should actually come from. The new pods will pick up the broken ConfigMap when they restart, so I need to fix it first with the correct variable substitution and seed hosts, then carefully restart es-cluster-2 without losing cluster quorum. Let me check how the ConfigMap is mounted in the StatefulSet to understand the restart strategy.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1804,"cache_read_input_tokens":32377,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1804},"output_tokens":28,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"28648cf1-1043-40a1-9d8b-bddeab7a3727","uuid":"8e21ac5b-ab40-4df0-9868-941b6a9898ea","request_id":"req_011CceySourKh7ahCfCYrWCm"}
