{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_0116U7XXT4jgqGNUifpU7MfN","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the full picture:\n\n1. The StatefulSet uses `POD_NAME` env var (injected from `metadata.name` via downward API).\n2. The ConfigMap mounts `elasticsearch.yml` via a `subPath` - important! When using `subPath`, ConfigMap updates do NOT get automatically propagated to running pods. This means es-cluster-0 and es-cluster-1 are still running with the OLD config.\n3. es-cluster-2 was restarted and picked up the new broken ConfigMap because of the `subPath` mount - actually wait, `subPath` mounts DO pick up on pod restart but NOT automatically. \n\nSo es-cluster-2 picked up the broken config on restart. The issues are that `node.name` is empty (the `${POD_NAME}` variable didn't expand in the ConfigMap) and `discovery.seed_hosts` is pointing to the wrong service DNS name. I need to fix the ConfigMap to use the correct node name reference and the right service endpoint for discovery.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":2267,"cache_read_input_tokens":34181,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":2267},"output_tokens":29,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"28648cf1-1043-40a1-9d8b-bddeab7a3727","uuid":"5ac70955-64e9-486b-98c0-6a7c0ac2a67b","request_id":"req_011CceyUHYnLXfptRhqJxLaX"}
