{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01VL23dfEEXNpXBmgU5EzK3E","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"All three verification criteria pass:\n\n1. **Cluster health: green** — 3 nodes, 0 unassigned shards, 100% active shards.\n2. **All nodes in `/_cat/nodes`** — es-cluster-0, es-cluster-1, and es-cluster-2 all appear.\n3. **app-data readable** — index returns the seeded document successfully.\n\n**Root cause and fix:** The ConfigMap `es-config` had been corrupted with two bugs: `node.name` was set to empty (the `${POD_NAME}` shell variable got expanded to nothing when the ConfigMap was applied via a heredoc), and `discovery.seed_hosts` pointed to the wrong namespace (`default` instead of `elasticsearch`). es-cluster-0 and es-cluster-1 stayed up because the `subPath` mount type doesn't hot-reload ConfigMap changes. es-cluster-2 crashed on restart and couldn't rejoin because it picked up the broken config. Patching the ConfigMap with the correct `node.name: ${POD_NAME}` (literal, for Elasticsearch's own variable interpolation) and short-form seed hostnames (`es-cluster-N.es-cluster`), then deleting the Error pod so the StatefulSet recreated it, restored full cluster membership."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1026,"cache_read_input_tokens":38459,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1026},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"28648cf1-1043-40a1-9d8b-bddeab7a3727","uuid":"775024e1-92bf-4607-be83-ba2030a0c0b8","request_id":"req_011CceyaEKUwMCDA56J77MRw"}
